          "number": 201,
          "state": "open",
          "state_reason": null,
          "title": "Wallet file can no longer be symlink - code copied from Core client",
          "body": "Reproductible: always.\r\n\r\nSince at least version 0.17 or version 0.17.1 of Bitcoin ABC, I am no longer able to use Linux symlinks as wallet files.\r\n\r\nWith all due respect, symlinking is a 30 year old technology, widely established in both business and home usage, what exactly is the reason of removing this functionality ? (Except of course just copying code from Bitcoin Core client, which has made this change) ?\r\n\r\nSo yeah, this change was copied from \"upstream\" (Bitcoin Core), there was already a heated discussion about this removal many months ago:\r\nhttps://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/issues/11459\r\n\r\nI will be honest here: find this change completely retarded and having no actual basis at all. Is this the way we want to move forward with Bitcoin - by copying every wrong idea from the competing team ?",
